                                            Apple TV+ may now be known as Apple TV, but it still offers a weekly selection of great movies to watch.  
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>This week's roundup of great movies to watch comes with a bit of news specific to this particular streaming service. In <a href="https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2025/10/apple-original-films-blockbuster-feature-f1-the-movie-from-joseph-kosinski-to-make-global-streaming-debut-on-friday-december-12-2025/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">a press release</a> announcing the premiere date of <em>F1 The Movie</em>, <a href="https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1&publisher_slug=howtogeek&u1=UUhtgUeUpU2017312&article_name=5+Apple+TV+Movies+You+Should+Stream+This+Week+%28October+13+-+19%29&article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fapple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-october-13%2F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftv.apple.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Apple TV+</a> has quietly changed its name, dropping the "+" and is now just "Apple TV."</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-october-13/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Naya Create Is the Specialty Keyboard System for When Time and Money Are No Object]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/naya-create-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bill Loguidice]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/01-2025-10-09-13-10-03.jpg" length="946" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Naya Create]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Naya Create is a premium modular keyboard system that encourages a new way to work. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>In a sea of me-too keyboard and mouse designs, it's refreshing when a product like the <a href="https://naya.tech/products/naya-create-3-0" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Naya Create</a> attempts to break the mold. Unfortunately, this modular keyboard system proves more enthusiast's experiment than something that's ready for the mass market.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/naya-create-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your PC Feels Slow? Microsoft Says These Two Windows 11 Settings Are to Blame]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pc-feels-slow-microsoft-says-these-two-windows-11-settings-are-to-blame/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/windows_11_generic_hero_1-jpg.jpg" length="136116" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[OneDrive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Configure these settings for a performance boost.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Everyone wants their Windows PCs to offer the best performance. Apps should open instantly, there shouldn't be any lag when switching windows, and the system itself should boot immediately. However, if any of these aspects feel a bit sluggish, Microsoft says it could be due to your OneDrive file syncing settings and your computer's visual effects.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-pc-feels-slow-microsoft-says-these-two-windows-11-settings-are-to-blame/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Enroll for Continued Windows 10 Security Updates]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-enroll-for-continued-windows-10-security-updates/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Timothy Jacob Hudson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/illustration-of-a-glowing-windows-10-logo-inside-a-blue-room-surrounded-by-security-shields-with-the-words-2026-updates-on-the-floor.png" length="551" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Official Windows 10 support is ending very soon, but if you aren't ready to upgrade, you can still enroll for security updates for another year.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>On October 14th, Microsoft will be officially ending support for Windows 10. However, if you aren't ready to upgrade yet, you can sign up for Extended Security Updates so you can continue getting important security patches beyond 2025. There are a few steps needed to enroll in ESU.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-enroll-for-continued-windows-10-security-updates/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Reasons Your Graphics Card Is Overheating]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-your-graphics-card-is-overheating/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/a-gpu-with-a-warning-icon.jpg" length="1796" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[GPU]]></category><category><![CDATA[pc building]]></category><category><![CDATA[Desktop]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Even a small issue can make your card run dangerously hot.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you've noticed your graphics card running hotter than usual, there are a few common culprits likely to blame. Modern cards often feature robust cooling solutions that help it maintain maximum clock speeds and performance, but some problems are simply inevitable with any GPU.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 19:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/reasons-your-graphics-card-is-overheating/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 Portable Apps That I Always Keep On a Flash Drive]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/10-portable-apps-that-i-always-carry-with-me-on-a-flash-drive/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chifundo Kasiya]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/06/person-s-hand-putting-a-usb-drive-in-a-laptop-port.jpg" length="898" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Get to work immediately wherever you go.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You never know when a certain Windows app can help solve an immediate problem. You may not always have time to download and install what you need. But luckily, there are several useful ones with portable versions that can fit on your thumb drive.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/10-portable-apps-that-i-always-carry-with-me-on-a-flash-drive/</guid></item></channel>
